uMkhonto weSizwe veterans in Durban are once again calling for the closure of foreign-owned shops. Courtesy of #DStv403 DURBAN - uMkhonto weSizwe veterans in Durban have again called for the closure of foreign-owned shops. The group said foreigners are a corrupting force and have contributed to the growth of social ills in the coastal city. READ: MKMVA members demand ANC keep its 'jobs promise' MKMVA KZN convener Zibuse Cele said once foreign nationals have been expelled from the country, social problems will end. Cele stated South Africans are being passed over for employment in favour of foreign nationals.